==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: commutativity
<hw>com`mu*ta*tiv"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Math.)</fld> <def>the property of a binary operation or operator
such that the result of one term operating on a second is equal to the
result of the second term operating on the first.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>GG</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ If the symbol ⟦ldquo⟧*⟦rdquo⟧ is taken to be a
commutative binary operator, then the following equation holds:
<mathex>a*b = b*a</mathex>

A common example is the addition operator for real numbers,
⟦ldquo⟧+⟦rdquo⟧: <mathex>a+b = b+a</mathex> </note>⟦br⟧
[<source>GG</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Commutator</ent>⟦br⟧
